The Rho Programming Language
============================

Rho (aka ρ) is an embedding programming language with lexical scoping and some modern semantics (hopefully). Rho has a stack-based VM called the Rho runtime and it looks like follows:

+-------------------------------------+
|            runtime (heap)           |
| +---------+ +---------+ +---------+ |
| | context | | context | | context | |
| | (stack) | | (stack) | | (stack) | |
| +---------+ +---------+ +---------+ |
+-------------------------------------+

A Rho runtime has more than one contexts and each context has its own stack for function calls and local variables. The runtime also maintains a global memory pool for objects less than 1kB and does garbage collection. Contexts are also scheduled by the runtime to execute bytecodes concurrently.

Rho is for learning purposes only and is under really slow development.

